      ],
      "content": "<ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;a name=\"BKMK_Intellisense\"&gt;</ph><ph id=\"ph2\">&lt;/a&gt;</ph>Intellisense"
    },
    {
      "content": "Added in ISE 3.0",
      "pos": [
        2079,
        2095
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Intellisense is an automatic\\-completion assistance feature that is part of <ph id=\"ph1\">[!INCLUDE[ise_2](../Token/ise_2_md.md)]</ph>.",
      "pos": [
        2099,
        2215
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Intellisense displays clickable menus of potentially matching cmdlets, parameters, parameter values, files, or folders as you type.",
      "pos": [
        2216,
        2347
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "What value does this change add?",
      "pos": [
        2351,
        2383
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "With the addition of Intellisense, it is easier to discover cmdlets and syntax when you use <ph id=\"ph1\">[!INCLUDE[ise_2](../Token/ise_2_md.md)]</ph> to create scripts.",
      "pos": [
        2387,
        2537
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "You can also use <ph id=\"ph1\">[!INCLUDE[ise_2](../Token/ise_2_md.md)]</ph> to learn <ph id=\"ph2\">[!INCLUDE[wps_2](../Token/wps_2_md.md)]</ph> while you create new scripts.",
      "pos": [
        2538,
        2673
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "What works differently?",
      "pos": [
        2677,
        2700
      ]
    },
    {
      "pos": [
        2704,
        2888
      ],
      "content": "When you type cmdlets in the <ph id=\"ph1\">[!INCLUDE[ise_2](../Token/ise_2_md.md)]</ph> 3.0 or later, a scrollable and clickable menu displays, allowing you to browse and select the appropriate commands."
    },
    {
      "pos": [
        2894,
        2930
      ],
      "content": "<ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;a name=\"BKMK_Snippets\"&gt;</ph><ph id=\"ph2\">&lt;/a&gt;</ph>Snippets"
    },
    {
      "content": "Added in ISE 3.0",
      "pos": [
        2933,
        2949
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "<bpt id=\"p1\">*</bpt>Snippets<ept id=\"p1\">*</ept> are short sections of <ph id=\"ph1\">[!INCLUDE[wps_2](../Token/wps_2_md.md)]</ph> code that you can insert into the scripts you create in <ph id=\"ph2\">[!INCLUDE[ise_2](../Token/ise_2_md.md)]</ph>.",
      "pos": [
        2953,
        3122
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "<ph id=\"ph1\">[!INCLUDE[ise_2](../Token/ise_2_md.md)]</ph> comes with a default set of snippets.",
      "pos": [
        3123,
        3200
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "You can add snippets by using the <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>New\\-Snippet<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> cmdlet while working in <ph id=\"ph1\">[!INCLUDE[ise_2](../Token/ise_2_md.md)]</ph>.",
      "pos": [
        3201,
        3316
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "What value does this change add?",
      "pos": [
        3320,
        3352
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "By using snippets, you can quickly assemble and create scripts to automate your environment.",
      "pos": [
        3356,
        3448
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "What works differently?",
      "pos": [
        3452,
        3475
      ]
    },
    {
      "pos": [
        3479,
        3621
      ],
      "content": "To use snippets in <ph id=\"ph1\">[!INCLUDE[wps_2](../Token/wps_2_md.md)]</ph> 3.0 or later, on the <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Edit<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> menu, click <bpt id=\"p2\">**</bpt>Start Snippets<ept id=\"p2\">**</ept>, or press <bpt id=\"p3\">**</bpt>Ctrl\\-J<ept id=\"p3\">**</ept>."
    },
    {
      "pos": [
        3627,
        3670
      ],
      "content": "<ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;a name=\"BKMK_AddOnTools\"&gt;</ph><ph id=\"ph2\">&lt;/a&gt;</ph>Add\\-on tools"
    },
    {
      "content": "Added in PowerShell 3.0",
      "pos": [
        3673,
        3696
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "<ph id=\"ph1\">[!INCLUDE[ise_2](../Token/ise_2_md.md)]</ph> now supports add\\-on tools, which are Windows Presentation Foundation (WPF) controls that are added by using the object model.",
      "pos": [
        3700,
        3866
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Add\\-on tools can be displayed as a vertical or horizontal pane in the console.",
      "pos": [
        3867,
        3946
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Multiple add\\-on tools in a pane are displayed as a tabbed control.",
      "pos": [
        3947,
        4014
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "You can also add or remove add\\-on tools that are produced by non\\-Microsoft parties.",
      "pos": [
        4015,
        4100
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "For more information about how to import or remove add\\-on tools, see <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Windows PowerShell ISE Operations<ept id=\"p1\">](http://technet.microsoft.com/library/cc732148.aspx)</ept>.",
      "pos": [
        4101,
        4259
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "What value does this change add?",
      "pos": [
        4263,
        4295
      ]
    },
    {
      "pos": [
        4299,
        4500
      ],
      "content": "Add\\-ons allow you to extend and customize <ph id=\"ph1\">[!INCLUDE[ise_2](../Token/ise_2_md.md)]</ph> with tools that can enhance your scripting experience or add functionality to <ph id=\"ph2\">[!INCLUDE[ise_2](../Token/ise_2_md.md)]</ph>."
    },
    {
      "content": "What works differently?",
      "pos": [
        4504,
        4527
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "<ph id=\"ph1\">[!INCLUDE[ise_2](../Token/ise_2_md.md)]</ph> 3.0 and later come with the <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Commands<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> add\\-on.",
      "pos": [
        4531,
        4620
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "The <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Commands<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> add\\-on allows you to browse cmdlets, and access help about the cmdlets side\\-by\\-side with the <bpt id=\"p2\">**</bpt>Script<ept id=\"p2\">**</ept> and <bpt id=\"p3\">**</bpt>Console<ept id=\"p3\">**</ept> panes.",
      "pos": [
        4621,
        4767
      ]
    },
    {
      "pos": [
        4769,
        4879
      ],
      "content": "Additional add\\-ons can be found by using the <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Open Add\\-on Tools Website<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> command on the <bpt id=\"p2\">**</bpt>Add\\-ons<ept id=\"p2\">**</ept> menu."
    },
    {
      "pos": [
        4885,
        4945
      ],
      "content": "<ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;a name=\"BKMK_RestartMgr\"&gt;</ph><ph id=\"ph2\">&lt;/a&gt;</ph>Restart manager and auto\\-save"
    },
    {
      "content": "Added in PowerShell 3.0",
      "pos": [
        4948,
        4971
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "<ph id=\"ph1\">[!INCLUDE[ise_2](../Token/ise_2_md.md)]</ph> now automatically saves your open scripts every two minutes, in a separate location.",
      "pos": [
        4975,
        5099
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "If <ph id=\"ph1\">[!INCLUDE[ise_2](../Token/ise_2_md.md)]</ph> stops working, or if the operating system is restarted, after <ph id=\"ph2\">[!INCLUDE[ise_2](../Token/ise_2_md.md)]</ph> restarts, it recovers scripts that were open in the last session, even if the scripts were not saved.",
      "pos": [
        5101,
        5347
      ]
    },
    {
      "pos": [
        5349,
        5479
      ],
      "content": "To change the automatic saving interval, run the following command in the console pane: <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>$psise.Options.AutoSaveMinuteInterval<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept>."
    },
    {
      "content": "What value does this change add?",
      "pos": [
        5483,
        5515
      ]
    },
    {
      "pos": [
        5519,
        5676
      ],
      "content": "You can now work within <ph id=\"ph1\">[!INCLUDE[ise_2](../Token/ise_2_md.md)]</ph> knowing that your open scripts are automatically saved in the event of an unexpected restart."
    },
    {
      "content": "What works differently?",
      "pos": [
        5680,
        5703
      ]
    },
    {
      "pos": [
        5707,
        5817
      ],
      "content": "<ph id=\"ph1\">[!INCLUDE[ise_2](../Token/ise_2_md.md)]</ph> 2.0 does not save the scripts automatically in the event of a restart."
    },
    {
      "pos": [
        5823,
        5870
      ],
      "content": "<ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;a name=\"BKMK_MRU\"&gt;</ph><ph id=\"ph2\">&lt;/a&gt;</ph>Most\\-recently used list"
    },
    {
      "content": "Added in PowerShell 3.0",
      "pos": [
        5873,
        5896
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "<ph id=\"ph1\">[!INCLUDE[ise_2](../Token/ise_2_md.md)]</ph> now has a most\\-recently used list for files.",
      "pos": [
        5900,
        5985
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "When you open a file in <ph id=\"ph1\">[!INCLUDE[ise_2](../Token/ise_2_md.md)]</ph>, the file is added to the most\\-recently used list on the <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>File<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> menu.",
      "pos": [
        5986,
        6122
      ]
    },
    {
      "pos": [
        6124,
        6270
      ],
      "content": "To change the default number of files in the most\\-recently used list, run the following command in the console pane: <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>$psise.Options.MruCount<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept>."
    },
    {
      "content": "What value does this change add?",
      "pos": [
        6274,
        6306
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "You can now use the most\\-recently used list to easily access your frequently\\-used files.",
      "pos": [
        6310,
        6400
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "What works differently?",
      "pos": [
        6404,
        6427
      ]
    },
    {
      "pos": [
        6431,
        6516
      ],
      "content": "<ph id=\"ph1\">[!INCLUDE[ise_2](../Token/ise_2_md.md)]</ph> 2.0 does not have a most\\-recently used list."
    },
    {
      "pos": [
        6522,
        6565
      ],
      "content": "<ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;a name=\"BKMK_ConsolePane\"&gt;</ph><ph id=\"ph2\">&lt;/a&gt;</ph>Console pane"
    },
    {
      "content": "Added in PowerShell 3.0",
      "pos": [
        6568,
        6591
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "The separate command and output panes that were available in the first release of <ph id=\"ph1\">[!INCLUDE[ise_2](../Token/ise_2_md.md)]</ph> have been combined into a single console pane.",
      "pos": [
        6595,
        6763
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "The console pane is similar in function and appearance to a typical <ph id=\"ph1\">[!INCLUDE[wps_2](../Token/wps_2_md.md)]</ph> console, but it includes the following enhancements (most are described in this topic).",
      "pos": [
        6764,
        6959
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Syntax coloring for input text (not output text), including XML syntax",
      "pos": [
        6965,
        7035
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Intellisense",
      "pos": [
        7041,
        7053
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Brace matching",
      "pos": [
        7059,
        7073
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Error indication",
      "pos": [
        7079,
        7095
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Full Unicode support",
      "pos": [
        7101,
        7121
      ]
    },
    {
      "pos": [
        7127,
        7157
      ],
      "content": "<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>F1<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> context\\-sensitive help"
    },
    {
      "pos": [
        7163,
        7208
      ],
      "content": "<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Ctrl\\+F1<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> context\\-sensitive Show\\-Command"
    },
    {
      "content": "Complex script and right\\-to\\-left support",
      "pos": [
        7214,
        7256
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Font support",
      "pos": [
        7262,
        7274
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Zoom",
      "pos": [
        7280,
        7284
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Line\\-select and block\\-select modes",
      "pos": [
        7290,
        7326
      ]
    },
    {
      "pos": [
        7332,
        7444
      ],
      "content": "Preservation of typed content at the command line when you press the <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Up<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> arrow to view history in the console"
    },
    {
      "content": "What value does this change add?",
      "pos": [
        7448,
        7480
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "The addition of these console pane changes provides a scripting experience that is more consistent with the console interface.",
      "pos": [
        7484,
        7610
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "What works differently?",
      "pos": [
        7614,
        7637
      ]
    },
    {
      "pos": [
        7641,
        7723
      ],
      "content": "<ph id=\"ph1\">[!INCLUDE[ise_2](../Token/ise_2_md.md)]</ph> 2.0 has separate command and output panes."
    },
    {
      "pos": [
        7729,
        7782
      ],
      "content": "<ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;a name=\"BKMK_CommandLine\"&gt;</ph><ph id=\"ph2\">&lt;/a&gt;</ph>Command\\-line switches"
    },
    {
      "content": "Added in PowerShell 3.0",
      "pos": [
        7785,
        7808
      ]
    },
    {
      "pos": [
        7812,
        7977
      ],
      "content": "If you start <ph id=\"ph1\">[!INCLUDE[ise_2](../Token/ise_2_md.md)]</ph> from the command line (by typing <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Powershell\\_ise.exe<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept>), you can add the following new command\\-line switches."
    },
    {
      "pos": [
        7983,
        8073
      ],
      "content": "<bpt id=\"p1\">*</bpt>\\-NoProfile<ept id=\"p1\">*</ept>: Starts <ph id=\"ph1\">[!INCLUDE[ise_2](../Token/ise_2_md.md)]</ph> without running <bpt id=\"p2\">**</bpt>$profile<ept id=\"p2\">**</ept>"
    },
    {
      "pos": [
        8079,
        8111
      ],
      "content": "<bpt id=\"p1\">*</bpt>\\-Help<ept id=\"p1\">*</ept>: Displays a Help window"
    },
    {
      "content": "<bpt id=\"p1\">*</bpt>\\-mta<ept id=\"p1\">*</ept>: Starts <ph id=\"ph1\">[!INCLUDE[ise_2](../Token/ise_2_md.md)]</ph> in multithreaded apartment mode.",
      "pos": [
        8117,
        8205
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "The default operation mode for <ph id=\"ph1\">[!INCLUDE[ise_2](../Token/ise_2_md.md)]</ph> is single\\-threaded apartment mode, or <bpt id=\"p1\">*</bpt>\\-sta<ept id=\"p1\">*</ept>.",
      "pos": [
        8206,
        8324
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "What value does this change add?",
      "pos": [
        8328,
        8360
      ]
    },
    {
      "pos": [
        8364,
        8505
      ],
      "content": "The addition of these command\\-line switches allows you to control the environment in which the <ph id=\"ph1\">[!INCLUDE[ise_2](../Token/ise_2_md.md)]</ph> runs."
    },
    {
      "content": "What works differently?",
      "pos": [
        8509,
        8532
      ]
    },
    {
      "pos": [
        8536,
        8628
      ],
      "content": "<ph id=\"ph1\">[!INCLUDE[ise_2](../Token/ise_2_md.md)]</ph> 2.0 does not recognize these command\\-line switches."
    },
    {
      "pos": [
        8634,
